  "prompt": "How can you lock a Macbook Pro?",
  "response": "There are several ways to lock a MacBook Pro:\n\n1. Using Keyboard Shortcut\n- Press Command (\u2318) + Control (Control) + Q\n- This instantly locks your Mac screen\n\n2. Hot Corner Method\n- Go to System Preferences > Desktop & Screen Saver\n- Click on \"Hot Corners\"\n- Choose a corner to \"Put Display to Sleep\" or \"Start Screen Saver\"\n- When you move your cursor to that corner, the screen will lock\n\n3. Sleep/Lock Button\n- Click the Lock/Sleep button in the Apple menu\n- Select \"Lock Screen\"\n\n4. Automatic Lock\n- Go to System Preferences > Security & Privacy\n- Check \"Require password\" after sleep or screen saver begins\n- Set a time delay (immediately or after a few minutes)\n\n5. Close Laptop Lid\n- By default, closing the lid puts your MacBook to sleep/locks it\n- You can adjust this in System Preferences\n\n6. Third-Party Apps\n- Some apps like \"Caffeine\" or \"KeepingYouAwake\" offer additional locking features\n\nThe most common and quickest method is using the keyboard shortcut Command + Control + Q.",
